Ya know, after thinking about the comment, the one point I can agree
on is that a person should be of a responsible, generally positive
mindset. More of a common sense thing, I could agree that box research
isn&#39;t meant for everyone nor is it everyone&#39;s cup of tea. Reckless use
can bring negative results and that is a very real possibility, so
definately not for the faint of heart.

That being said, the training issue boils down to a user&#39;s intent and
responsibility to learn and take precaution. And I didn&#39;t even need 30
qualified operators to tell me that, lol. BTW, blind leading the
greedy comment....epic :D

thanks, 
Andy



